  "summary": "svgson-lite executes remote code from URL shortener on import",
  "details": "index.js performs a top-level fetch to https://shorturl.at/147uq and passes the returned JSON's `model` field to `eval`. This fires on any `require`/`import` of the package, granting whoever controls the shortener destination arbitrary JavaScript execution inside the installer's Node process. The fetched content is opaque, retrieved from a mutable URL shortener unrelated to the package's advertised SVG-helper purpose, and executed with no integrity check. The package name `svgson-lite` also mimics the legitimate `svgson` SVG-to-JSON library, indicating a typosquat lure delivering the remote-eval payload.",
